the way I was raised. I was shielded from reality. I was taught that the good guys always win and that there is a natural order to nature that makes us better than the wild animals. But with my contact with a wider culture that has suffered that same conditioning I’m changing my opinion on how we evolved on this planet. Those who helped us were predators who killed our ancestors. They used the waste of that predator to evolve our capacity to reason. And the jury is still out on whether that is all to our own detriment.

We are a high functioning species but we tend to use reason first, and that makes us very slow to respond to reality. It has taken a long time for science to dominate the attitude of teaching. If you doubt the effects of religion just look at the Saudis teaching their children the importance of theism. It is a sad time when the so-called educated population is so reluctant to accept the truth of science, especially if it contradicts their religious books.

When it comes to a nuclear winter, all that matters is the size of the first bomb. Urban planners think in terms of megatons per square mile, because that is the area they want to protect. Once you go past a megaton on the ground, most things are toast. Life’s too short to waste it on trivia.

“human extinction from nuclear winter.” That’s the big one. It’s “only” a Prussian Blue pill, if we’re a species ready to take it
